The OpenMath connectivity in Axiom 2.3 was based on the latest version
of the INRIA C Library cited in the paper by Dalmas et al.  Since NAG
doesn't own that library and I was unsure of whether its license
conditions would be acceptable to the open source community I disabled
the code which linked with it in the version of CCL I sent to
Arthur/Tim.  The library itself is freely available from the link
http://www.openmath.org/cocoon/openmath/software/OMCv1.4a.tgz.

The support for translating Axiom to OpenMath (which doesn't depend on
the INRIA Library) wasn't extensive - we basically wanted to have the core
OpenMath content dictionaries supported but its not too hard to extend
that.  Going e.g. "OMwrite sin(x)" should return a string containing the
OpenMath encoding of sin(x).

Mike.

On Fri, Dec 06, 2002 at 10:20:34PM -0500, Tim Daly wrote:
